      <h5>Documentation:</h5>
      <p>
        MongoDB is a cross-platform, document oriented database that provides,
        high performance, high availability, and easy scalability. MongoDB works
        on concept of collection and document.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b> Database:</b> It is a physical container for collections. Each
        database gets its own set of files on the file system. A single MongoDB
        server typically has multiple databases.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>Collection:</b> It do not enforce a schema. Documents within a
        collection can have different fields. Typically, all documents in a
        collection are of similar or related purpose.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>Document:</b> It is a set of key-value pairs. Documents have dynamic
        schema. Dynamic schema means that documents in the same collection do
        not need to have the same set of fields or structure, and common fields
        in a collectionâ€™s documents may hold different types of data.
      </p>

